  The pipeline takes ~10 seconds. What if user sends a 
  message 3 seconds after going idle, right as the 
  pipeline starts?

  SOLUTION: Pipeline is cancellable. On new message:
  - If pipeline hasn't started → cancel, continue session
  - If pipeline is mid-execution → let it finish in 
    background, start new session with OLD graph state.
    Pipeline results apply to NEXT session start.
  - Never block the user. Worst case: one session delay 
    on memory updates.

