  SOLUTION: Force a "soft boundary" at 200 messages.
  - Flush all scribes and run librarian
  - BUT don't reset the conversation
  - Reload updated MAP into agent context mid-session
  - Agent gets a memory refresh without the user noticing
  - This is like the brain's "micro-sleeps" — brief 
    consolidation without full sleep

EDGE CASE 3: Very short session (1-2 messages)
  SOLUTION: Don't run full pipeline for trivial sessions.
  - If < 3 messages, skip librarian/dreamer
  - Just save the scribe deltas for next session
  - Next session's librarian processes accumulated deltas
  - Prevents graph churn from "hey, never mind" sessions

